cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper presents an approach to model features and function nets of automotive systems comprehensively, which is a software engineering problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with modeling automotive systems and their functions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the paper may involve the use of AI techniques to validate the feature views against the complete function nets. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possibility as the paper mentions the importance of developers having a good overview and understanding of the functions affected by changes in requirements. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not seem to be related to sound or acoustics.
